Here’s a clean, practical manual based on your document. I simplified it into something you can actually follow step-by-step without getting lost.

🧠 SUMMARY (Read this first)

You are installing ownCloud Infinite Scale (OCIS) using Docker Compose on a server.

Big picture flow:

Prepare server (Ubuntu + Docker)
Configure domain + DNS
Download deployment files
Edit .env configuration
Start containers
Fix errors (certificates, DNS, ports)
Access via browser

👉 Goal: have a working cloud system at
https://your-domain.com

✅ CHECKLIST (Before you start)
🔧 Server & System
 Ubuntu 22.04 or 24.04 installed
 SSH access working
 sudo permissions
 At least:
 4–6 GB RAM
 ~3 GB disk space
🐳 Software
 Docker installed
 Docker Compose installed
 unzip installed
🌐 Network
 Public IP (or port forwarding)
 Ports open:
 22 (SSH)
 80 (HTTP)
 443 (HTTPS)
 Domain name purchased
🌍 DNS
 Domain points to your server IP
 Subdomains ready:
 ocis.yourdomain.com
 (optional) collabora.yourdomain.com
 (optional) onlyoffice.yourdomain.com
📧 Email (optional but recommended)
 SMTP_HOST
 SMTP_PORT
 SMTP_SENDER (required or it won’t start)
🚀 STEP-BY-STEP INSTALLATION
1. Update server
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y
2. Install required tools
sudo apt install unzip -y
3. Download OCIS example (on your local machine)

Download from:
https://download-directory.github.io?url=https://github.com/owncloud/ocis/tree/stable-8.0/deployments/examples/ocis_full

4. Upload to server
scp ~/Downloads/your-file.zip user@your-server:/opt
5. Extract on server
mkdir -p /opt/compose/ocis/ocis_full

unzip -d /opt/compose/ocis/ocis_full \
/opt/your-file.zip
6. Enter directory
cd /opt/compose/ocis/ocis_full
7. Edit configuration (.env)
nano .env
🔑 IMPORTANT SETTINGS
Security
# Comment this line
# INSECURE=true
Email for certificates
TRAEFIK_ACME_MAIL=you@email.com
Use staging certificates first
TRAEFIK_ACME_CASERVER=https://acme-staging-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory
Domain
OCIS_DOMAIN=ocis.yourdomain.com
Optional apps
COLLABORA_DOMAIN=collabora.yourdomain.com
ONLYOFFICE_DOMAIN=onlyoffice.yourdomain.com
Email (minimum required)
SMTP_SENDER=noreply@yourdomain.com
8. Validate config (optional but smart)
docker compose config
9. Start system
docker compose up -d
🔍 VERIFY INSTALLATION
Check containers
docker compose ps
Check logs
docker logs -f <container_id>

👉 First check:

traefik logs (certificates)
then ocis logs
⚠️ COMMON ERRORS & FIXES
❌ Certificate error

Cause: invalid email

Contact emails forbidden

✅ Fix:

TRAEFIK_ACME_MAIL=real@email.com
❌ Domain not working
NXDOMAIN

✅ Fix:

Check DNS
Domain must point to your IP
❌ Certificate generation fails
acme challenge error

✅ Fix:

Open ports 80 and 443
🔄 After fixing errors (IMPORTANT)
docker compose down
docker volume rm ocis_full_certs
docker compose up -d
🔐 Switch to real certificates (FINAL STEP)
Stop:
docker compose down
Edit .env:
# Remove staging server
TRAEFIK_ACME_CASERVER=
Delete cert volume:
docker volume rm ocis_full_certs
Restart:
docker compose up -d
🌐 ACCESS YOUR SERVER

Open browser:

https://ocis.yourdomain.com
Default login:
User: admin
Password: admin
🛠️ USEFUL COMMANDS
Stop system
docker compose down
Restart
docker compose up -d
View containers
docker ps -a
View logs
docker logs -f <container_id>
🧩 OPTIONAL (ADVANCED)
Move data outside Docker (recommended for production)
docker cp <container_id>:/var/lib/ocis/. /mnt/data
docker cp <container_id>:/etc/ocis/. /mnt/config

chown -R 1000:1000 /mnt/data /mnt/config

Then update .env:

OCIS_DATA_DIR=/mnt/data
OCIS_CONFIG_DIR=/mnt/config
🎯 FINAL RESULT

You will have:

A self-hosted cloud (like Google Drive)
Web office integration
Secure HTTPS (Let’s Encrypt)
User management (built-in IDM + IDP)